<TITLE> UK, France, Germany ready fin markets text </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 LISBON, Oct 19 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - British Prime Minister Gordon Brown, German Chancellor Angela Merkel and French President Nicolas Sarkozy are working on a joint position on the financial markets, a British source said on Friday. The source, who declined to be identified, said it was unclear whether any statement would be ready for release at an EU summit in Lisbon where the three leaders were meeting. The leaders discussed recent market turmoil and Europe's response to globalisation at their session on Friday, touching on issues such as how to deal with sovereign wealth funds, transparency in complex financial instruments and currencies. As they met, the euro traded close to its historic highest level against the US dollar. Sarkozy and Merkel sent a joint letter to EU president Portugal in September, calling for more transparency in financial markets with "suitable regulatory and monitoring mechanism
